TITLE: Safe Object Reference Implementation Pattern
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the correct way to implement object references to avoid circular dependency issues by separating reference creation and implementation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hayes/pothos/blob/main/website/content/docs/guide/circular-references.mdx#2025-04-18_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// May cause issues
export const User = builder.objectRef<IUser>('User').implement({...});

// Should be safe
export const User = builder.objectRef<IUser>('User')

User.implement({...});
```

