TITLE: Extended Options for Field Subscriptions - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Expands upon field subscriptions by introducing filtering and cache invalidation options for the 'answers' field in a 'Poll' object. It enables re-fetching capabilities and control over subscription-triggered updates.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hayes/pothos/blob/main/website/content/docs/plugins/smart-subscriptions.mdx#2025-04-18_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
builder.objectType('Poll', {
  fields: (t) => ({
    question: t.exposeString('question', {}),
    answers: t.field({
      type: ['Answer'],
      canRefetch: true,
      subscribe: (subscriptions, poll) =>
        subscriptions.register(`poll-answers/${poll.id}`, {
          filter: (value) => true | false,
          invalidateCache: (value) => context.PollCache.remove(poll.id),
        }),
