TITLE: Registering Subscriptions for Objects - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to register subscriptions for a 'Poll' object type. For each 'Poll' object, a subscription is registered based on the poll's id, enabling dynamic subscription management as poll objects are included in query results.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hayes/pothos/blob/main/website/content/docs/plugins/smart-subscriptions.mdx#2025-04-18_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
builder.objectType('Poll', {
  subscribe: (subscriptions, poll, context) => {
    subscriptions.register(`poll/${poll.id}`)
  },
  fields: (t) => ({
    question: t.exposeString('question', {}),
    answers: t.field({...}),
  }),
});
```

