TITLE: Customizing Input Type Names in Pothos with-input Plugin
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to customize the naming convention for input types using the typeOptions.name configuration in the with-input plugin. Demonstrates removing Query/Mutation prefix from input type names.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hayes/pothos/blob/main/packages/plugin-with-input/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import WithInputPlugin from "@pothos/plugin-with-input";
const builder = new SchemaBuilder({
  plugins: [WithInputPlugin],
  withInput: {
    typeOptions: {
      name: ({ parentTypeName, fieldName }) => {
        const capitalizedFieldName = `${fieldName[0].toUpperCase()}${fieldName.slice(1)}`;
        // This will remove the default Query/Mutation prefix from the input type name
        if (parentTypeName === "Query" || parentTypeName === "Mutation") {
          return `${capitalizedFieldName}Input`;
        }

        return `${parentTypeName}${capitalizedFieldName}Input`;
      },
    },
  },
});
```

